# CursorClaw — Tools & Dependencies

## ACP JSON-RPC Gotchas

- `id` and `result` can be `0` or `null`. **Never use truthy checks**
  (`if (id)` / `if (result)`). Use `!= null` or structural checks.
- Cursor CLI extension methods come in two prefixes: `cursor/` and `_cursor/`.
  Always match both; normalize `_cursor/` → `cursor/`.
- Any incoming JSON-RPC request with an `id` that you don't handle must
  still be acknowledged, otherwise the agent process hangs.
- `session/update` has multiple subtypes: `agent_message_chunk`,
  `agent_thought_chunk`, `tool_call`, `tool_call_update`. Cover all of them
  (at minimum log unknowns) or tool-call phases become a black box.
- Stream promise chains must have `.catch()` on every link. A missing catch
  causes `finalize` to never execute.
- `session/new` must not default `mcpServers: []` — omit the field entirely
  when no MCP servers are configured.

## Feishu (Lark) SDK

- `@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk@^1.32.0` provides `client.im.message.update()`
  for streaming reply updates on a single message.
- Interactive card (`interactive` msg_type) schema has not been fully
  validated in this project. On production errors, fall back to the stable
  `post` message type.

## Telegram Bot API

- `node-telegram-bot-api@^0.67.0` provides `sendMessage`,
  `editMessageText`, `sendChatAction`, `getFileLink`.
- Telegram message limit: 4096 chars. Use `splitMessage()` for long texts.
- Use `markdownToTelegramHtml()` + `parse_mode: 'HTML'` for rich formatting;
  fall back to plain text on parse errors.

## Prompt Timeout

- Default ACP prompt timeout: 5 minutes (`DEFAULT_PROMPT_TIMEOUT_MS`).
  On timeout, `cancelCurrentPrompt()` sends `session/cancel` and returns
  the partial response accumulated so far.

